    "created_at": "2012-01-16T05:49:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-16T05:49:55Z",
    "body": "On 64-bit platforms, the state field is 64-bit.\nHowever, in generated LLVM code the state field in _rust_mod_map is still 32-bit.\nWhen runtime calls update_module_map, it writes 64-bit data into a 32-bit location.\nOn FreeBSD, it overwrites a global variable that is used in getenv function and results in segfault.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
